    <PrimAttribute name="chargeDays" id="969cae0b-71c6-4d51-ad50-e811b452fc0a">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Integer"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>Future storage only, the number of days or months, depending on the chargeDaysType, to charge in advance.</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="chargedDaysType" id="61437fdb-bc88-4bc3-882c-d06ca1693229">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Integer"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>
RELEASE STORAGE
One of the class constants 
	Calendar_Days (all days, elapsed days) charge for all days, the difference between 2 dates.
	Working_Days (days which the port works, determined by the configured calendar), difference between 2 dates then adjust by looking at the working calendar.
	Working Days and Compulsory Days (compulsory Days are adhoc days for when the port is closed due to weather events etc.), difference between 2 dates then adjust by looking at both calendars.
 
FUTURE STORAGE
One of the class constants 
	Calendar_Days (all days, elapsed days), number entered is how many days in the future to create a future storage transaction for
	Calendar_Months (elapsed months), number entered is how many months in the future to create a future storage transaction for
	Working_Days (days which the port works, determined by the configured calendar), number entered is how many days in the future then adjust by looking at the working calendar.
	Working Days and Compulsory Days (compulsory Days are adhoc days for when the port is closed due to weather events etc.), number entered is how many days in the future then adjust by looking at both calendars.
	</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
